    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>FUEL INFLATION IN BRAZIL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazilians will pay about 11.3 percent more at gasoline pump beginning July 15 because of government adjustments in prices to reflect rising cost of fuel (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Starting on Saturday, Brazilians will pay about 11.3 percent more at the gasoline pump because of government adjustments in prices to reflect the rising cost of fuel. At the wholesale level, the government increased gasoline and diesel prices by 15 percent, while kerosene, used as jet fuel, lost a government subsidy and jumped 34.5 percent. Butane gas, which most Brazilians use for cooking, will increase 18 percent.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
